 The candidate of the Peoples Democratic Party PDP, Chimaobi Ebisike, has been declared winner of Saturday’s bye-election for Aba North and Aba South federal constituency. He polled 10, 322 to defeat his closest rival, Mascot Uzor Kalu, of the All Progressive Congress, APC. Details later… Vanguard News Nigeria   All rights reserved. This material and any other digital content on this platform may not be reproduced, published, broadcast, written or distributed in full or in part, without written permission from VANGUARD NEWS.